+# Technology Stack Guidelines
+
+## Backend Technology Stack
+
+### Core Framework
+- **Node.js with Express.js**: Use Express.js for the REST API server
+- **TypeScript**: Use TypeScript for type safety and better development experience
+- **PostgreSQL**: Use PostgreSQL as the primary database
+
+### Key Libraries
+- **pg**: PostgreSQL client for Node.js
+- **express-validator**: For request validation
+- **cors**: For Cross-Origin Resource Sharing
+- **helmet**: For security headers
+- **morgan**: For HTTP request logging
+- **dotenv**: For environment variable management
+
+### Development Tools
+- **nodemon**: For development server auto-restart
+- **jest**: For unit testing
+- **supertest**: For API testing
+- **ts-node**: For running TypeScript directly
+
+## Frontend Technology Stack
+
+### Core Framework
+- **React**: Use React with functional components and hooks
+- **TypeScript**: Use TypeScript for type safety
+- **React Router**: For client-side routing
+
+### UI Library
+- **Material-UI (MUI)**: Use Material-UI for consistent, professional UI components
+- **@mui/material**: Core Material-UI components
+- **@mui/icons-material**: Material-UI icons
+
+### State Management
+- **React Context + useReducer**: For simple state management (avoid Redux for this small project)
+- **React Query/TanStack Query**: For server state management and caching
+
+### Development Tools
+- **Create React App**: For project bootstrapping
+- **React Testing Library**: For component testing
+- **jest**: For unit testing
+
+## Database Design
+
+### Schema Naming Conventions
+- Use snake_case for table and column names
+- Use singular nouns for table names (project, bug)
+- Use descriptive column names (created_at, not created)
+
+### Data Types
+- Use SERIAL for auto-incrementing primary keys
+- Use VARCHAR with appropriate limits for text fields
+- Use TEXT for long descriptions
+- Use TIMESTAMP for date/time fields
+- Use ENUM types for status and severity fields
+
+## Project Structure
+
+### Backend Structure
+```
+backend/
+├── src/
+│   ├── controllers/     # Route handlers
+│   ├── services/        # Business logic
+│   ├── models/          # Data models and types
+│   ├── middleware/      # Express middleware
+│   ├── routes/          # Route definitions
+│   ├── database/        # Database connection and migrations
+│   └── utils/           # Utility functions
+├── tests/               # Test files
+├── package.json
+└── tsconfig.json
+```
+
+### Frontend Structure
+```
+frontend/
+├── src/
+│   ├── components/      # Reusable components
+│   ├── pages/           # Page components
+│   ├── hooks/           # Custom React hooks
+│   ├── services/        # API service functions
+│   ├── types/           # TypeScript type definitions
+│   ├── utils/           # Utility functions
+│   └── contexts/        # React contexts
+├── public/
+├── package.json
+└── tsconfig.json
+```
+
+## API Design Principles
+
+### REST API Guidelines
+- Use RESTful conventions for endpoints
+- Use appropriate HTTP methods (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
+- Use consistent response formats
+- Include proper HTTP status codes
+- Implement proper error handling
+
+### Response Format
+```json
+{
+  "success": true,
+  "data": {},
+  "message": "Optional message"
+}
+```
+
+### Error Response Format
+```json
+{
+  "success": false,
+  "error": {
+    "message": "Error description",
+    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
+    "details": {}
+  }
+}
+```
+
+## Development Workflow
+
+### Git Workflow
+- Use feature branches for development
+- Write descriptive commit messages
+- Keep commits focused and atomic
+
+### Code Quality
+- Use ESLint and Prettier for code formatting
+- Write unit tests for critical functionality
+- Use TypeScript strict mode
+- Follow consistent naming conventions
+
+### Environment Management
+- Use environment variables for configuration
+- Separate development, testing, and production configs
+- Never commit sensitive information to version control
\ No newline at end of file


